description: Demolition of existing buildings and erection of a mixed use development providing a total of 193 residential units (of both private and affordable tenure) including houses and apartments, with associated amenity space including gardens, balconies and terraces; a new health centre (Class D1 use) (1,873sq.m), a pharmacy (Class A1 use) (94sq.m), two commercial units (flexible Class A1/A2/A3 or B1 use) (189sq.m), within buildings ranging between two and five-storeys high, together with the provision of hard and soft landscaping, enhanced pedestrian routes, and associated car parking and cycle parking, with the development proposed to be constructed in two phases.
